traffic.phaseplan

Class PhasePlan

  • java.lang.Object
    • traffic.phaseplan.PhasePlan
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FullyActuatedPhasePlan, PretimedPhasePlan

    public abstract class PhasePlan
extends Object
implements Serializable
    An abstract class encapsulating features common to all kinds of phase plans. In particular, all phase plans encapsulate an algorithm for controlling the progression from phase to phase. No objects of this abstract (generic) class may be created. Concrete extensions of this class MUST implement the two abstract cycle methods so that objects can be constructed. Extensions may also override other methods to specialise the behaviours of the generic version. A phase plan needs to know the various phases in the plan, their order and the current phase.
    Author:
    (C) Neville Churcher
    See Also:
    PretimedPhasePlan, FullyActuatedPhasePlan, Serialized Form

      • nextPhase

        public Phase nextPhase()
                throws Exception
        Reports the next phase in the plan. Does not actually advance to the next phase. Cyclic -- after last phase, returns first again.
        Throws:
        Exception - if valid phase not found.
        See Also:
        advance

      • advance

        protected void advance()
                throws Exception
        Performs housekeeping duties as the plan advances to its next phase. Updates the plan's information about which is the current phase, how many phases have been completed and so on. Does not involve directly any traffic stream or signal control activities.
        Throws:
        Exception - if phase not found.
